            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Cal Raleigh, catcher for the Seattle Mariners, is having a historic 2025 season in Major League Baseball. In the latest game, he hit two home runs, reaching 60 homers for the season and helping the Mariners clinch the American League West title.</p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">He is the first catcher ever to reach 60 home runs in a season and only the seventh player overall to do so. Over the course of 2025, Raleigh has broken multiple records. He surpassed Ken Griffey Jr.'s franchise home run record for the Mariners.</p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">He also broke Salvador Pérez's record for most homers in a season by a catcher (48). As a switch hitter, he also eclipsed Mickey Mantle's single-season record of 54 homers by a switch hitter.</p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Raleigh's power surge has attracted comparisons with all-time greats, and he is a strong candidate for the MVP award. Analysts have noted that his pace puts him in rare company: only a handful of players in MLB history have reached 60 home runs.</p>
            
